To:   Sarah MurphyFrom:   SarahSubject:   Memory filesDateline:   foreverBut sometimes the logic finds a tiny crack in the bars and slowly, grain by grain, escapes into the deep wide wildernesses, leaving only a thin shell of itself behind to guard the pain.And of course, the pain, freed from its overly pedantic jailor, goes on holiday. It cannot afford the south of France, so it settles for a wild beer bash, hauling down keggers filled with hopped up spasms, glugging down warm fire gulps of cheap gallows wine.Then I come in, knocking heads, and bellow:  The pain is of the mind the mind refuses to acknowledge the pain,therefore there is no pain.##higher##lower___________________Sarah/ Moon/ Laurel___________________